        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-01T19:52:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This pattern feels a little strange to me. I would much prefer having main call a helper function with the flag values that we can inject here from tests. Heck, that helper can have an output writer that we can more easily intercept rather than overwriting os.Stdout. We wouldn\u0027t have to use osExit either.",
      "revId": "9f53203064e212c1b5673fb3a88c64ba77c686a6",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f27d91e2_01af6e80",
        "filename": "perf/nanostat/main_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 32
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-01T20:21:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e This pattern feels a little strange to me. I would much prefer having main call a helper function with the flag values that we can inject here from tests.\n\nThat wouldn\u0027t test parsing the flags.\n\n\u003e Heck, that helper can have an output writer that we can more easily intercept rather than overwriting os.Stdout. We wouldn\u0027t have to use osExit either.\n\nThat would require changing every fmt.Print* call to fmt.Fprint*, while doing it this way keeps the main code\nreadable and clear, while still allowing it to be tested.\n\nThis test structure was copied from benchstat, which inspired this program:\n\nhttps://github.com/golang/perf/blob/d949658356f9a1d750bdabd650745c5bd5f1cfa4/cmd/benchstat/main_test.go",
      "parentUuid": "f59f29a1_a858b9ed",
      "revId": "9f53203064e212c1b5673fb3a88c64ba77c686a6",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3fdbd700_98ebf0db",
        "filename": "perf/nanostat/main_test.go",
        "patchSetId": 32
      },
      "lineNbr": 36,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-01T20:45:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e That wouldn\u0027t test parsing the flags.\n\nMaybe add a specific test that focuses on that part if that\u0027s important.\n\n\u003e That would require changing every fmt.Print* call to fmt.Fprint*, while doing it this way keeps the main code\nreadable and clear, while still allowing it to be tested.\n\nThere are 2 such calls that would need to be changed.\n\nThe reason I requested this change was because it was very difficult for me to understand what the test was doing and that the test was testing the right things. I would like our tests to be easy to read and easy to understand.",
      "parentUuid": "f27d91e2_01af6e80",
      "revId": "9f53203064e212c1b5673fb3a88c64ba77c686a6",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
